      "text": "Stopping narco-terrorism from the Caribbean to the Eastern Pacific.\n\nAfter surpassing 200K+ lbs of cocaine seized through Operation Pacific Viper, @USCG has surged counter-drug operations into the next gear. Last week, Coast Guard Cutter Seneca offloaded 17,750+ lbs of cocaine seized in the Eastern Pacific, and crews at Station Fort Lauderdale seized 745 lbs from 2 vessels off Port Everglades.\n\n80% of U.S.-bound drug interdictions occur at sea vice land. That’s our finest maritime fighting force, defending U.S. borders and maritime approaches and keeping deadly drugs out of our communities.\n\nRead more here: https://t.co/8F3L5uPPta\n\n#USCG #OperationPacificViper #MaritimeSecurity #HomelandSecurity\n\n@DHSgov @USCGPACAREA @DeptofWar",
      "text_resolved": "Stopping narco-terrorism from the Caribbean to the Eastern Pacific.\n\nAfter surpassing 200K+ lbs of cocaine seized through Operation Pacific Viper, @USCG has surged counter-drug operations into the next gear. Last week, Coast Guard Cutter Seneca offloaded 17,750+ lbs of cocaine seized in the Eastern Pacific, and crews at Station Fort Lauderdale seized 745 lbs from 2 vessels off Port Everglades.\n\n80% of U.S.-bound drug interdictions occur at sea vice land. That’s our finest maritime fighting force, defending U.S. borders and maritime approaches and keeping deadly drugs out of our communities.\n\nRead more here: https://www.news.uscg.mil/Press-Releases/Article/4406849/coast-guard-offloads-over-1335-million-in-illicit-drugs-interdicted-in-eastern/\n\n#USCG #OperationPacificViper #MaritimeSecurity #HomelandSecurity\n\n@DHSgov @USCGPACAREA @DeptofWar",
